# 🦁 Animal Classification using K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

## 📌 Objective  
Classify animals into different categories using the **K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)** algorithm.  

## 📊 Dataset  
- **Dataset:** Zoo Dataset  
- **Features:**  
   - Hair, Feathers, Eggs, Milk  
   - Airborne, Aquatic, Predator  
   - Legs, Tail, Domestic  
   - Animal Type  

## 🧠 Techniques Used  
- **Data Preprocessing:**  
   - Handled missing values  
   - Removed outliers  
   - Scaled numerical features  

- **KNN Classification:**  
   - Split data into training and testing sets (80-20)  
   - Used different values of **K** to tune the model  
   - Chose an appropriate distance metric (e.g., Euclidean)  

## 🔍 Analysis and Interpretation  
- **Key Hyperparameters:**  
   - `n_neighbors` – Number of nearest neighbors  
   - `metric` – Distance metric (Euclidean, Manhattan, Minkowski)  

- **Evaluation Metrics:**  
   - Accuracy  
   - Precision  
   - Recall  
   - F1-Score  

## 🚀 Results  
- **Accuracy:** Achieved high classification accuracy  
- **Insights:**  
   - KNN performed well with optimal K value  
   - Distance metric affected the model’s performance  
